messages.content:
The partygoers enter the great hall of the Golden Castle. There are dozens and dozens of people, making it hard to make out everyone, but all 3 of you are counted among their number. Emperor Aragon III stands on the second floor balcony overlooking the great hall with Sir Triden at his side.

"Welcome... Welcome, one and all. To this... Special occasion. My advisors have told me this party is sure to be an exciting one. As always it's an honour to be your Emperor and to... Invite you all into my castle." Aragon gestures vaguely at people. "Please... Make full use of the first floor and enjoy the things the servants are carrying out. I'm pleased to see some... Faces I haven't seen in a while. Thank you all." He nods with thinly veiled disinterest.

Yyeeeess, that would check out. I take a glass of wine or somesuch from one of the servants and down it quickly. “Mmm.” I make this noise. 

How tedious, the triviality with which minutiae of social decorum is operated… yet such a thing is a necessity for long term sustenance of ideology. I take a seat or lean against a wall.
Nash nods along robotically to whatever the Emperor is saying, which... he was probably fully listening. Yeah! Yeah.

There's a guy walking around in servant-attire with an alcoholic beverage. Nash grabs it and downs it. "Blehh..." He makes this noise, sticking out his tongue, then quickly looks around to make sure no one noticed him doing that.

*I check that my gloves are on and my clothes covering my arm properly... After that I adjust my contact lenses and take a good look around me, with intent of spotting who I need to spot. Still, the Emperor, I sometimes pity him, what with all the people around him being a bunch of rats that espouse rotten rubbish all day long. Gah, I'm losing myself in my thoughts again, I need to get a grip!* 
I put on a nice smile and walk to a servant with a drink in order to appear... normal. Of course, I only pretend to be drinking.

Imperial Prince Asturian calls out to Aragon from the crowd with a wry smile. "To you too as well, brother! It truly is an honour to be back here... Work had just been keeping me so busy!"

People are slowly scattering to other places in the castle, such as the ballroom, dining room, or courtyard.
Nash looks around for someone he even vaguely knows. He's walking sort of in the direction of the courtyard, but could be waylaid at any moment.

*Asturian. That sack of shit. He's important, I need to figure out a way to get something out of him. But if he's talking to the Emperor, then now isn't a good time in case I draw attention to myself.* 
I put away the drink and start collecting my thoughts in regards to who else I may recognise here. 
*Laura is here... I'm not sure if it would be a good idea to interact with her, I don't want to anyone to draw any links between us. It would... be troublesome.*
"Selle" spots that people are scattering everywhere. 
*I need to decide where to go. I can't dilly-dally like a buffoon* 
I keep a mental note of where Asturian is and walk towards the dining room. 
*Finding members of the Edwardson family might be of use as well... I have to keep an eye out.*

Indeed. What a curious state of affairs, very strange indeed… ballroom, one of those words you don’t contemplate ever too closely. A ball is an orb, a sphere, a tool used for recreation… perhaps we all are playing a game right now. Perhaps we are all of balls. Dust to dust.

I head to the ballroom in order to accomplish my important goals of brownnosing different elites with my impeccable wit and charm.
"Hey, pal!" Selle feels their arm be grabbed by a man who should distinctly not be allowed anywhere near this party.
((holyshit

I try my best to not be startled by being two things. One, the fact that I know this man, and... his rottenness. Two, the fact that he just grabbed me and luckily it was not the right arm...
*Ugh, Donald... I can't pretend to know him, he doesn't know that it's me in disguise. I can't afford to give myself away here.*
"Hello there, can I help you sir?" I put on a nice smile to hide my discomfort.
*It's probably fine if he figures out that it's me but... Drawing attention to myself with how active he is is not a good idea for now... I'll do my best to keep it lowkey here.*
(( he looks so fucking skrunkly in that picrew
"The name's Donald Jameson! I'm something of a philanthropist y'know?" He chuckles. "Was just taking a look around when I realized I've never seen you before... What's your role in this town?"

"Just a bit of a humble novel editor, I work with book publishers in Soltaria. I've got some good friends around these parts so I've been humbly accepted to His Majesty's celebrations... But enough about me, a philanthropist you are? How admirable! You must do a lot of work for society. it's very nice to meet you." 
*This is awful.*
"What kinda books? I've always been an avid reader, maybe I've seen your work!"

"Haha... well, I'm just a editor, but I've worked on lots of different works, from retellings of history for children to mystery novels written for adults. Like Egepha Triskie, we helped edit her mystery novels and change mistakes in them or spot errors in the writing. And Then There Were Some is quite the well written book, and Egepha is a very talented author, I'm sure as an avid reader you could appreciate her work."
*Publishing companies are full of people and authors tend to republish their works with different ones... So this is fine.*
"You mention you are an avid reader, what kind of books are you particularly a fan of?"
(( Should I be rolling deception here?
((Yeah, sure. I forgot to ask for those I haven't D&Ded in a while whoops))
"Ah, gotcha, gotcha..." He seems disappointed.

Selle looks at the man in confusion as he seems to have ignored her question, as if he was looking to get something from her lie.
*He was so fucking onto me, this sneaky bastard. I gotta be careful around him.*

Selle can spot the Duchess talking to Harriet further into the dining room.

"I'm a reader of all sorts. You read Wazy Emerson before?" Donald.

*The Edwardson's are over there.* I keep a mental note of that.
"Of course I have. Anyone who knows a fair share about literature has dabbled in his work a little."
"Probably a wise guy, yeah."

"He has certainly left his mark on society. I've heard his death is quite tragic. what with him losing his memory before his death. But anyway, I'm feeling quite hungry. Why don't we go enjoy the lovely food given to us by the royals today?" 
*I attempt to pivot from the topic.*
"Sure, sure... Enjoy!"
I step back a bit to survey the area, to see who is around.

*This place reeks of privilege, eugh. Donald would perhaps be a pleasant person if he wasn't such a conniving fox. His intentions always stink of mischief and his cute little face doesn't help how much people love him.*
*Now where did I spot the Edwardson's. A high priestess and a duchess is pretty much as high as you can go. These are powerful, powerful people though, so I must be careful.*
I walk a little bit closer to them, but not up to them. About as close as I can barely hear them speak. I once again grab a drink to appear friendly.
The Duchess is attempting to make small talk with her daughter. Harriet is barely responsive. It's not a very interesting conversation.

*This is kind of a nostalgic feeling.* Selle gets slightly melancholic hearing what seems like a stereotypical conversation between a mother and a daughter at a gathering. *Ugh! Snap out of it. Now's not the time to be feeling down about something. This is useless. I need to wait for them to seperate or for something to happen.*
(( would I be able to cast Minor Illusion somewhere else to take people's attention away from themselves
(( or is it really obvious if i cast magic
((Depends on what the spell says))
(( Somatic or Material
((range 30ft
((Sure))

I make sure my hand is under the table where I am sat and gesture it to cast Minor Illusion, and make a sound appear as though a bee had gotten into the dining hall and was buzzing around loudly, although nobody could see it. The sound moves around the dining hall and passes by the Edwardson's towards the window.

Harriet leaps up in place and takes out her rapier in a panic.

The Duchess sighs. "It’s a bug, dear. Put that away."
(( how long is the party on for by the way
((The whole night))
alright

*Hahaha... This is fun. But actually, this is good information. I can see that Harriet is much more susceptible to wanting pulling out her weapons at the sign of a threat, and I know. She is incredibly strong. I should be careful, perhaps it's not yet a good idea to talk to them.*
*Enough messing around, I should try to walk around more before I make any sharp decisions, I can always return. Perhaps I can spot Asturian.* 
Selle leaves their drink on the table and walks towards the dining room exit back where they came from.
Aeolian approaches as Selle gets up.
The most immediately noticeable thing in the ballroom is this woman putting on the worst dance moves Aeolian has seen in his life.
That’s good. For her. “Your skills are striking, madam.” I nod. “I hold great respect for the calisthenic arts.”

She just laughs at you.

"Don't try getting close to her, Burr." Washington Hamill approaches you.
“Hrm. Why not?”
"'Cause she's a bastard. And I don't want 2 problems for the Duchess fusing." Washington.

“I can hardly see how her parentage is relevant here. Bastards can be quite important. You may be behind the times; an abnormal person is the very emperor of this land.” 
I twirl the now empty glass in my hand. “Unless you mean a more colloquial ethical sense of the phrase, in which case I would note that I assume that as a given here.”
"...Ugh. I'm giving you a word of advice here, Burr. She may be nobility, but her uncle's the heads of the Craig Family. She's just asking for trouble."
“Our leader certainly casts a wide net of acquaintanceship. Should I expect Linjamin here? Hah. Lineage isn’t everything, Hamill.”
"Who is Linjamin?"
“Nothing important. I can afford to heed your advice in this one case, however. Talk less.” I shrug.

He sighs and walks away.

At this point Aeolian can notice the last notable person in this room.
Exactly. I approach her. “A rather ostentatious gathering, is it not?”
"Ah, hello Alia. I knew you wouldn't miss this."

“Naturally.” My lips curl upward. “At such a convergence of important figures… relevant developments are an inevitability, the dialectic… I simply don’t want to miss the show. I’m in awe that Asturian has materialized.”
"It is rather odd. Perhaps he expects to get something out of it?"
“Incredibly suspect. I only hope whatever power play he is trying at remains within the bounds of the law.”
"Well, who would know about the law better than the Emperor? Hehe..."
“Perhaps no one. Or someone, if the delegation is spread minutely enough. I fail to have a read on Aragon’s individual competency.”
"Well, my father speaks highly of him. He doesn't do that easily."
“So I have noticed. Though relying on the perception of others — or the perception of the perception of others — can only get one so far.”
She laughs politely.
I become incredibly uncomfortable at this for reasons not worth scrutinizing whatsoever. “Mm. I have no desire to take up your time unduly. It was good to see you, Ms. Skylar.”
"Likewise, Alia."
I nod politely and exit the ballroom.
My impeccable dancing skills shall be saved for another occasion.
Asturian and Aragon are the only notable people in the great hall.
“Your grace.” I bow respectfully to the emperor as I pass by on my way to the dining hall.
Aeolian bumps into this man as he enters the dining hall. He does not look even remotely important enough to be in attendance here.
“Hello. My apologies.” This man could very well be extremely important.
"You, you're the... Baron, right? Nice to meetcha."
“Yes. Aeolian Burr.” I extend a hand.
He takes it. "I'm Donald Jameson. You might've heard of me!"
“I have not.”
"That's a shame! I'm something of a hero of the people. You know what philanthropy is, right?"
“Yes.”
"That's my specialty. I don't really do it for rich guys like you, but your people probably love me."
“I see. A respectable pursuit.”
"Sure is. Feel free to ring me up if that brilliant mind of yours ever goes broke."
“Okay.” I nod.
He leaves.
I continue into the dining hall.
Selle is seated at a table. The Duchess and Harriet are nearby, with the latter having drawn her rapier for some reason.
“Curious.” I note this as being curious. I sit down near the person I don’t recognize because I do not particularly like The Duchess or want to get stabbed.
Selle tries to get up as he approaches.
I stare at the attempted departure coinciding with my arrival. “Was it something I said…?” I quip cleverly. I have not said anything. This is the joke.

*This person looks incredibly familiar. Is this the person who created that one material... Canadium? Erebonium? I can't put my finger on it.*
"Hello, can I help you?" I smile.

“I wouldn’t know. I’m unfamiliar with you. Apologies if you are some sort of esteemed philanthropist outside my own purview. I simply wished to sit and not be stabbed. I hope this can be accommodated.”

"Esteemed philanthropist?" *I strongly hold in my laughter after being reminded of Donald Jameson and resist making a joke at his expense.* I lightly chuckled "Haha, I'm sure the latter can be accommodated for you, Mr. Burr." *I remembered his name.* "But it's nice to meet you here, I do know of you as an inventor" *And a fucking landlord.*

“Yyyes, although, it can often be reductive to categorize people so narrowly. Americium… it may be the building block of the future, but blocks are nothing without builders.” 
I look vaguely into the air. “Architects and engineers and construction workers… I won’t ask you to place yourself in a box for me, thusly. But a name may be helpful, if this interaction continues.”

"Selle Mann. But just Selle is okay. I quite agree with you on that point. This world is nothing without people, and neither is the future. Perhaps my views on this topic are not to be disclosed in a space such as this one, however, for I am but a humble book editor gracefully invited here through the generosity of my acquaintances and His Majesty's benevolence." 
*I don't know much about this guy. The fact that he owns land in the empire is a red flag and had previously made a bad impression on me... I should keep talking to him.*
((btw should i be hiding Selle's thoughts
((nah that’s a personal choice I usually don’t gaf some people do))

“Intriguing. Books. A noble profession. It is good to break up the insularity of these sorts of groups, I think… I was beginning to grow exhausted with the familiarity of almost all faces here. The nobility has a bad habit of staying amongst themselves, even to the point where it causes them harm.” I make an expression of some disgust. 
“Though, that word itself is archaic… At any rate, Selle…”
I stare at THE DUCHESS. “Were you witness to the context wherein Lady Edwardson’s associate drew her weapon? I do doubt it was actually relevant to me personally.”

*That was my doing. It's good that it seemed to work as a distraction for people.*
"It seems like a bee or something of the sort had made it's way into the dining hall earlier. That's what caused Lady Harriet Dana to draw her rapier. I would be careful startling her."

"Either way, I would be careful with speaking ill of the nobility in these quarters, for quite obvious reasons." *Luckily we are at the entrance to the dining hall and there aren't many people here to hear us... I should not allow my thoughts to come out as much, as much as I want to rant about how much I hate some of this filth. My primary goal here is simply information.*
“I don’t tend to do ‘careful’. Covert, maybe.” I shake my head. “A rapier would not be effective against a bee at all. You would miss.”
"Haha, you might be right, but don't underestimate her skill."
"One wrong step and perhaps you could be the bee yourself"
"I'm sure with your amount of. Let's say, covertness, that you would be fine, however."
“Yes… ‘Bee yourself’. I always intend to. And in that sense, I am the Queen.” This might not mean anything whatsoever.

*This guy is so unserious it's unbelievable.*
"Well then, Queen Burr, what kind of relationship to the Emperor do you have?"
"Or perhaps a better question would be what your attitude is towards him"

“I do not know him all too well. I have some respect for the tribulations he must operate under. Of course, as someone whose authority supersedes mine, he plays the role of an enemy within my game theory. But that’s nothing personal. For now, while the potential conflict between us is a distant future, I wish him the best. Even if his choices may vex me.”

"I do agree that his, circumstances, are quite unfortunate. Perhaps we should be glad that it is him that is Emperor and not his twin brother, god forbid I say another word." *God I fucking hate that piece of shit so much. Speaking of him, I need to make sure I find him later.*
“It is odd that Asturias is here at all. None I have spoken to seem entirely aware of his aims at this event.”

*Well. It's incredibly convenient for me.*
"His motives are always incredibly strange. He doesn't seem particularly welcome here either. I can only imagine that he has something up his sleeve"
“I pity those in attendance unready to potentially witness a major historical event.”

*Oh it'll be a major historical event alright. If I get the chance his head is going kablooey. Unfortunately that's not happening so I just need to keep an eye on him.*
"I do feel as though tonight will be a very important night. Dozens of the most important people in the empire gathered all in one place." *I go back to my previous way of speaking as to not appear suspicious.* "I truly am blessed to be here for it."
“Indeed.” I fidget. “Incidentally, are you aware of a man named Donald Jameson?”

*Oh for fucks sake-*
"Yes, I am. I met him earlier today and he seemed to be quite interested in me. A philanthropist with an interest in Wazy Emerson? That's how he came off to me."
*It's honestly such a jumpscare for that name to come up. I know he's highly ranked in the Hellhounds but does he have to be here? I feel like I'm walking on thin ice everytime he's around.*
"I see. I was not aware of him prior to today. Curious."
"He seems like quite the admirable guy. I wonder if the Emperor has a sweet spot for his philanthropy."

"*Trust thyself: every heart vibrates to that iron string. The integrity of your own mind is sacred above all else. Endure the torture of the red-headed bard.* I'm quite fond of Emerson myself." I look around the room. "I wonder..."
(( THE RED HEADED BARD

I get up. "This environment is a touch stifling. Perhaps some fresh air would do me good." The attempts thus far to politically fraternize have gone less than ideally. "And there are still those I might anticipate at this event I have yet to locate..."

*I should probably head back into the hall and investigate the other areas. Aeolian's call for fresh air is a good idea.*
"Well then. It was nice talking to you, Aeolian. Perhaps I should read more Wazy Emerson, myself."
“Yes. So go back to the books.” I nod politely, and then exit the dining hall, having eaten nothing.
*What a strange individual.* I wait, then exit the dining hall too, going in a direction different from Aeolian.
Selle spots Asturian heading down a hallway alone. ((Roll insight))
Selle can’t figure anything else out about Asturian.
*I can't grasp his intentions. But I can probably follow him anyways. I need to be stealthy though.*
((Roll stealth))
Asturian descends down into the basement, where no one else should be.

*Where is he going? This seems like the perfect chance to find something out. Good* 
I follow.
He continues down a few more hallways before arriving at a dead end. “Shit, did I make a wrong turn…"
((sorry my responses might be a bit slow rn
Selle flicks their hand and casts Minor Illusion, making it seem like the ceiling above Asturian is crumbling. (sound)
He backs away nervously. "Do you need my voice to open!?"
*He almost spotted me there.*
*He really does seem like he's looking for some sort of hidden room... As long as I stay hidden this could be good...*
"Dammit!" He starts trying to push bricks at random to no avail. He pulls out a map and looks at it, looking angry.
(( can i roll perception to try and see the map
(( or is it investigation
((Perception))
(( i should have put more points into wisdom smh
Selle can’t fully see it without getting too close, but it seems like a map of the castle.
*I can't see well enough. What's so special about that map? It's clear he's looking for something but it just seems like a regular map of the castle. Maybe I should fuck with him.*
He puts the map away and starts to walk in Selle's direction.
*Shit shit!* Selle casts Minor Illusion again with a flick of their wrist and makes the wall say Asturian's name in a distorted voice
He stops… Before running at the wall and trying to use the momentum to crash through it. He fails and falls flat on his back.
*Holy shit he is actually falling for it. I should use this for something useful.*
*But I think I might need to back up, otherwise I could get caught.*
He gets up and pulls out a knife, trying and failing to scratch out the connections between the bricks.

Selle casts minor illusion with a flick of their hand and the wall says to Asturian: "Asturian, I have been waiting. For this wall to open for you, you must first state your purpose of being here." In a distorted voice.
((Roll deception))
"My birthright! It’s supposed to be here! My right to rule!"

*So he's still chasing that huh... He must have a grudge against Aragon. But what does he mean by "his right to rule?" he speaks about it like it's some sort of existing object that he can gain and become ruler. Is there some sort of signed declaration giving him this right? I can do something here*
Selle casts Prestidigitation, making the wall glow with the flag of Soltaria and feel warm to the touch.
*This is a great situation, but far too close for comfort. I may be in disguise but I don't want this shitface to recognise me.*
He tries pushing on the wall, to no avail. "What do you want from me!? I deserve this!"

Selle once again casts Minor Illusion, and the wall speaks to Asturian: "Asturian, to claim your birthright to rule, you must first profess this to LIbra. Confess all of your sins in the ballroom of the Golden Castle, and you shall be atoned for and granted the right to rule by Libra herself."
Selle prepares to back up.
"Ugh, what a sick joke! I have no such sins!" He storms away in the direction of Selle.
Selle casts Prestidigitation in front of Asturian, with a bright spark in his eyes, then runs in a direction where Asturian wouldn't be able to spot them.
*Fuck! That didn't work! I guess his ego is too high for that.*
((should i roll stealth or acro or something
((Stealth yeah))
"You! Have you been mocking me!?" Asturian grabs Selle as they try to run. ((Roll initiative))
It’s Selle's turn.
(( is this combat
((Yes))
"Me!? I'm nothing but a humble book editor!" Selle casts Fire Bolt at Asturian's feet.
(( how do i roll damage
((It’s written on the spell. In this case 1d10))
(( what's the hit/dc thing
((To hit this spell it’s 1d20+int))
(( ah ok
(nat 20)

It crits, meaning double damage. Asturian is immediately knocked out from the hit, ending combat. 

((50xp))
(( LOOOL
*What a hassle. What do I do with this guy now.*
Selle casts Prestidigitation to clean up the char on his clothes.
Asturian is laying on the floor.
(( can i roll perception to check him for damage on his body
(( or can i just. look at him since he's knocked out
((Depends on what you’re looking for))
(( like any obvious signs of a fight
Yes he is visibly injured.
*Well since he's knocked out I might as well search his body for something.*
((Roll investigation))
Asturian has a map, a knife that’s as powerful as Selle's, jewels at a total value of 5gp, and 5 business cards.
*Business cards? Are these of AMO related people?* Selle takes out a book and an ink pen and writes down the details of the 5 cards.
They’re copies of his business card.
*Wait, what am I doing! This is just his shitty ass business card. Ugh, he has nothing of use on him.*
*I'll just take a look at his map that he had.*

It’s a map of the castle dungeon, with an x on the spot they’re at.

Selle hears a scream from upstairs.

*There's something special here. Somehow. Even though I'm pretty sure this wall is just a sham. Either way, something strange is happening upstairs. I'll just have to leave him here. He shouldn't remember my face.*
Selle puts Asturian slumped upright against the wall, with the map in his hands, then leaves to go upstairs.
I am heading to the court yard.
Sir Jonald Triden is in the courtyard.

Fascinating. I gaze into the night sky, or not that if it isn’t night. I have no real conversation topics to initiate with Triden, but this is fine. An artistic mind is content with the company of one.

How banal these events are. My time could be much better spent. …My emersonian mind is already bored with the stars, that’s how bored I am. I approach Jonald Triden.
“Good day, general.”
"Chin up, sonny."
“Pardon?”
"Life ain’t always…" He says a completely unwritable word of gibberish. “A Tuesday." He makes a square with his fingers.
“…Intriguing.” I nod. “But the week recurs on a regular basis.”
He stands there silently looking at Aeolian.
“I respect your opinion all the same.”
"You ever heard. Corn Pop?"
“No. I have not.”
He was a sort of waving motion with his fist.
“A foe of yours? I’m uncertain if you’re referring to a person or thing.”
“I loved that man like a son…"
“I see. Apologies if I have dredged up unpleasant memories.”
"Corn pop was a bad dude. Who- Who ran a bunch of bad dudes."
“I see. Not a cleanly defined positive relationship, then. I understand. Often I have cared for those I could not endorse ethically.”
"He killed a-" He looks shocked by something. "You ever- A Tuesday."
“Hm.” I’m obviously unearthing some unhandled trauma, here. What day of the week is today, incidentally?

It’s Sunday. 

He points at Aeolian. "You’re her wi- Husband."
“Me?” I point to myself. “I am unmarried.”
"Shit… Is it today?"
“Today is Sunday.”
He starts counting with his fingers.
I allow him to do this.
He lifts up 8 fingers proudly.

“Exactly.” I nod. This would be Sunday’s position in the week, enumerating the first day of the week which begins it as Sunday. “I should have expected a sharp mind such as yourself would have a firm understanding of modular arithmetic.”
He nods. "I’m not ready to retire."
“A respectable choice. As you were, then.” I make to leave, having extracted all the wisdom from my elders I feel I can right now.
He walks away.
Alright. No one else in the courtyard?
There are other people but none that strike Aeolian as noteworthy. With the exception of Aliza, who is carefully balancing on the railing overlooking much of the city.
Ah. That’s good. I approach her and smile. “…Hello.”
"Hey! Looking for someone?"
“Not anymore. I was worried you’d skipped out on this.” I take care not to interrupt and disturb her… thing.
"Dad made me come. It wasn’t my first choice to hang around a bunch of greedy nobles."
“That sounds about right.” I chuckle. “Repute aside, the power of the nobility is a truth of the world as it exists. There are times where it is profitable to wade through the dirt.”
"What about the people wading through dirt every day?"
“They are too preoccupied with their own sense of profit, I suppose.”
"Like you?"
I smirk. “Such biting rhetoric. But the only way to remain free of dirt is to spend all one’s time in ivory towers.”
"The poors can’t afford that."
“No they cannot. Not enough ivory. Not yet, at least.”
"And where shall you fetch them more ivory!"
“The annals of potential.”
"Truly? I expected you to say you’d build it out of that fancy new material of yours."

“Tch.” I look around to ensure no one is overly close to our conversation. “You know as well as I that Americium isn’t sustainable as the primary construction material on that high of a scale. It would be like attempting to bake a cake with only eggs, write a song using only percussion. The ‘ivory’ here largely already exists. It’s merely a problem of extraction & distribution.” I lean against the railing. Her man Aeolian is on the ledge and shit.
She chuckles.
“I understand a desire to not compromise your morals. There are those I would not consider having dealings with. Even if my boundary is likely more… flexible, than yours.”
"Like criminals?"
“Essentially.”
They hear a scream from inside the castle.
“Oh no.” Aeolian turns towards the castle.
Aliza hops off the railing and rushes inside.
I follow her.
Kori Edwardson is being led around the courtyard by Viscount Oswalda Kapelput, aka your mother.
Ah, good. Nash power-walks towards them.

"Naaaaash!" Kori waves.

"Good morning, Nash." Oswalda bows politely.
Nash smirks. "Morning, my utterly ridiculous family. I'm surprised you two got an invite..!" Said mockingly.

"What?" Oswalda.

"Where have you beeeen!?" Kori.
"Oh, around!" Nash says, trying to look cool and sophisticated while twirling his wineglass. "You know. Building connections, socializing, the like."

Kori looks at him blankly. "Well, mom is being a bother." 

"Kori, I'm just trying to show you around..." Oswalda speaks nervously.
Nash laughs. "Are you sure you're not bothering *her*? Honestly, Kori..."

"No, really it's not a bother..." Oswalda.

"Well, I want to be alone right now either way." Kori.

"Don't be so spoiled, Kori." Nash says, still swirling around the wine. He takes another sip and then his face instinctively crumples up again. "Honestly, how do you make yourself drink this swill, mother?"

"..." Kori goes silent.

"Oh, it's a force of habit, dear..." Oswalda puts on a polite smile.

"Well, it's gross." Nash says petulantly. "I'm going to walk around and try and find more people to socialize with... spread the word of the Goddess, if possible. You're welcome to follow, Kori." He says the second part in a deeply mocking tone, as if he already expects her to trail behind him like some kind of lost duckling.
Then he walks away. Is Kori following?
Kori tries to but Oswalda stops her.
Nash looks back. "Is it really more important that she follow *you* around, mother...?"
"The Duchess asked of me to do this..." Oswalda.
"Ah." Nash says, discomforted. "Right. And for what purpose..?"
